article.headline: Montana State 72, San Jose State 59
article.story: BOZEMAN (AP) -- Montana State's starting guard tandem of Ja'Ron Jefferson and Branden Miller combined for 36 points and 10 rebounds Tuesday as the Bobcats beat San Jose State 72-59. The victory was the third in the row for Montana State (4-6) and avenged an earlier 1-point loss to the Spartans (3-6) last month in San Jose. Jefferson scored 19 points and had three rebounds. Miller, who scored 12 of his 17 points in the first half, had seven rebounds. San Jose's Marquin Chandler led all scorers with 22 points. The Spartans, who trailed most of the game, pulled to 43-39 on Eric Bloom's short jumper with 12:36 left. The Bobcats answered with an 8-point run and led 51-39 on Casey Durham's steal and layup with 10:28 remaining. Chandler's dunk cut the lead to 51-41 with 10:07 left, but MSU outscored the Spartans 11-4 over the next 4 minutes and 7 seconds and held a 62-45 advantage following Marvin Moss' jump shot with 6 minutes left. Nick Dissly had 13 points for Montana State and Alex Elam scored 17 for San Jose.
